""""""""""Aesthetics
:highlight Hint font: bold 11px "Consolas", monospace !important; margin: -.2ex; padding: 0 0 0 0px; outline: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, .5); background: rgba(255, 248, 231, .9); color: black; text-transform:uppercase;
:highlight TabNumber font: bold 14px "Consolas", monospace; margin: 0px; padding-right: .3ex; cursor: 3efault;


""""""""""Bindings
"Scrolling
:map -builtin j 13j
:map -builtin k 13k

:map <S-J> :tabprev<CR>
:map <S-K> :tabnext<CR>

"Copying stuff. We lose the ability to stop the page from loading...
"We also lose insert/caret/textarea mode but I don't think I care about them sufficiently anyways
:map <C-c> <C-v><C-c>

"For sites which support arrows for navigation (e.g. outlook). Plus, what do I
"use arrows for in normal mode?
:nmap <Left> <C-v><Left>
:nmap <Right> <C-v><Right>
:nmap <Up> <C-v><Up>
:nmap <Down> <C-v><Down>

"Lose the ability to do the auto-increment url thing, but selecting all
"but not sure how else I might select all easily
nmap <C-a> <C-v><C-a>

"Insert mode hacks... not sure what the better hotkeys would be
:imap -builtin <C-a> <C-v><C-a>
:imap -builtin <C-v> <C-v><C-v>
:imap -builtin <C-z> <C-v><C-z>

"private window
:map <C-S-n> :private<Space>winopen<CR>

"Add dictionary to alt-shift-d
:map <A-S-d> :tabopen<Space>dictionary<Space>


""""""""""Quickmarks
:qmark o www.outlook.com/owa/microsoft.com
:qmark g www.gmail.com
:qmark s www.stackoverflow.com
:qmark w www.weather.com/weather/today/Redmond+WA+98052:4:US
:qmark m www.metafilter.com


""""""""""Hints
"use chars instead of the silly number system
:set hintkeys=asdfjklertuioxcvnm

"Remove the hint text
:highlight Hint::after content: attr(number) !important;

""""""""""Site-specific
"gmail tabbing
:set passkeys+=mail.google.com:<C-]>,<C-[>
:set passkeys+=stackoverflow.com:<Tab>

""""""""""Misc
"Set startpage.com as the default search when using :open/:tabopen
:set defsearch=ixquick

"tab numbers (#gt)
:set guioptions+=n

"visual bell
:set visualbell

"Fix hinttags so it finds more elements
:set hinttags=:-moz-any-link,area,button,iframe,input:not([type=hidden]),label[for],select,textarea,[onclick],[onmouseover],[onmousedown],[onmouseup],[oncommand],[tabindex],[role=link],[role=button],[contenteditable=true],a[href]
